('537','1','0','Did you find the envoys of The Argus Wake?'),
('538','1','0',NULL),
('539','1','0','You were given direct orders to attack the Azureload Mine. Your reasons for loafing about Tarren Mill better be good or I will behead you for treason.'),
('540','6','6','I wish I could search the ruins too, but I fear these bones wouldn\'t hold me during my climb up the mountains. However, how does your hunt for knowledge progress, $N?'),
('541','1','0','Dun Garok proves to be too much of an obstacle for you, $C? And here I thought you had established yourself valiantly in Hillsbrad.$B$BIf you\'re not up to handle the mission assigned to you, I will find another who can produce better results. As for you, well, I am sure the Dark Lady could always use more grave diggers back in Tirisfal Glades.'),
('542','6','6','$N, you\'ve returned! How did your foray into Alterac go? Did you bring anything back with you?'),
('543','1','1','Salutations, $N. Do try to avoid stepping on my pant cuffs. This outfit is newly tailored.'),
('544','0','0','Did you find the thieves?  And more importantly, did you find what they stole?'),
('545','1','0','Have you yet thinned the Dalaran patrols around their ruins?'),
('546','6','6','So the lucky $N returns? How many humans have you slaughtered today? Hundreds I do hope!$b$bHave you any skulls for me?'),
('547','6','6','Were you able to retrieve my sword, $N? High Executor Darthalia will hang me from the rafters if she discovers my folly.'),
('549','1','0','Do you have nothing better to do than stand here before me, $c? As High Executor, I have more pressing matters than to stare at your rotting visage.'),
('550','1','0','What brings a $C all the way to the Undercity from the battlefield?'),
('551','1','0','Oh. You have something you\'d like me to look at? Some scrap of lore gathered from up in the mountains, I hope...'),
('552','6','6','Have you recovered Helcular\'s Rod yet? There are so many Yeti in this region, it will be very difficult to locate. But we must have it in order to proceed.'),
('553','1','0','Helcular\'s grave teems with a mystical energy.'),
('554','1','0','More interruptions?$B$BAh, this parchment is covered with a very intricate, finely woven spell. I can untangle it, of course, but it\'s going to take time. And time is very valuable to me...$B$BPerhaps I will just purchase it from you?'),
('555','1','0','Any luck finding the ingredients? I\'ll tell you, this territory isn\'t the peaceful place it once was. Ah, if only this unrest never occurred...'),
('556','0','0','Do you have the Worn Stone Tokens, $N?  The Magus is eager to unlock their secrets.'),
('557','0','0','Hello, $N. Elementals are tough quarry, but I know you\'re up to the task. Do you have those bracers of binding?'),
('558','0','0','Someday, I wanna be a hero just like Jaina... well, a boy hero that is.'),
('559','1','0','Did you get those heads for me, $N?'),
('560','1','0','Greetings, citizen. Have you come to lend your arm to upholding the safety of Southshore?'),
('561','1','0',NULL),
('562','1','0','I\'ve a letter ready to go to Major Samuelson in Stormwind. All I need are the results.'),
('563','1','0','Greetings, citizen. May the Stormwind city guard be of assistance?'),
('564','1','0','Mountain Lions killin\' off our horses left and right and here you are wantin\' to jibber-jabber about the weather and what not.$B$BOught to go and find myself a real hero. More killin\' and less talkin\'.'),
('565','1','0','So you have returned to the great Bartolo. Perhaps you have finished gathering the materials needed for your Yeti Fur Cloak? Or maybe you just enjoy basking in the greatness of me, Bartolo!'),
('566','6','6','Ah, $N. Perhaps you\'ve come to collect the bounty on the head of Baron Vardus?'),
('567','1','0','Yes?'),
('568','1','0','Our supply efforts are still being hampered by the indigenous raptor population, $c.'),
('569','1','6','Have you made any progress with the ogres of the Mizjah Ruins yet, $C?'),
('570','6','6','What news do you bring?'),
('571','6','6','Has fortune been on your side, $N? Were you able to obtain an aged gorilla sinew?'),
('572','6','6','Did your gathering efforts prove fruitful?'),
('573','6','6','I am almost ready to complete the enchantment. Have you performed my bidding?'),
('574','1','0','Sergeant Yohwa tells me you are skilled and brave, $C. Do you have something to report?'),
('575','0','0','My equipment is all ready to go, $n, I just need those skins. We don\'t want to keep Riddlevox waiting, that\'s for sure.$b$bIt\'s not a good idea for anyone to keep the chief inventor of the Tinkers\' Union unsatisfied.'),
('576','3','3','Ahoy, me bucko!  Might not be able to see but I can smell ye from halfway across port.$b$bCould really use me eye back.  Captain\'s going to keelhaul me when he finds out me peeper is in the hands of them dirty Bloodsail Buccaneers.$b$bWhat good is a lookout who can\'t see?  The crow\'s nest used to be me home...without me deadlights I\'d be lucky to scrub the bilge.'),
('577','1','0','Drizzlik\'s Excelsior leather boots, finest workmanship, one-hundred percent high quality saltwater crocilisk skin boots. None finer!$b$bCan\'t beat a glowing description like that, can you?$b$bExcept, maybe, if you have those skins for me?'),
('578','1','0','The trolls truly possessed some amazing magical objects, $N. And now, perhaps, I have the opportunity to add one to my extensive collection. Did you have any luck finding the source of the rumor?'),
('579','1','1','King Varian has placed great importance on learning, and thus has provided funds for making copies of various tomes and writings available to the public. It\'s very simple. You bring me a library scrip, and I can give you a copy of one of the available books.'),
('580','5','5','Sink me!  I\'m almost outta booze here!  Cap\'n is goin\' to weigh anchor and Ol\' Slim will be caught dry as the Tanaris Desert.  And once he discovers his port is missing. . . blimey!'),
('581','0','0','$C. Show me you have made prey of the Bloodscalp tribe.$b$bShow me your trophies.'),
('582','1','0','$N. I fear for our chief\'s son. Do you have the shrunken heads so I may inspect them?'),
('583','1','0',NULL),
('584','1','0','The greenish broth within the cauldron bubbles.'),
('585','0','0','I await the skulls...'),
('586','1','0','Although my own flesh boils off my skull, I can still smell your fear.$B$BHah!  You will never complete my task...'),
('587','6','6','Any luck finding the goods, matey?'),
('588','1','0',NULL),
('589','1','0','Do you have the shards, $N? They are needed for my final ritual, after we have the Mind\'s Eye.'),
('590','1','0',NULL),
('591','1','0','Greetings, $N. The spirits sing praise of your bravery, yet they tell me no tales of your quest against Mai\'Zoth.$b$bDo you have the Eye?'),
('592','1','0','$N. Kin\'weelay told me you set out to capture Yenniku.$b$bIs it true? Do you have him?'),
('593','1','0','Yenniku stands stunned before you, his mind in another place...'),
('594','1','0',NULL),
('595','1','0',NULL),
('596','0','0','The Bloodscalps will one day be crushed by the Darkspears! Do you have the necklaces of our doomed foe?'),
('597','1','0',NULL),
('598','0','0','The Skullsplitters will curse the day they brought us to war! Is your task complete?'),
('599','1','0',NULL),
('600','0','0','Do you have those crystals?? I need them!!$b$bI mean...I need to know the evil Venture Company is losing ground in Stranglethorn. Because, you know, we honest folk have to make a living!'),
('601','1','0','Have you had any luck, $N?'),
('602','1','0','If you wouldn\'t mind, I am rather busy right now.'),
('603','1','0',NULL),
('604','6','6','Ahoy, $n.  What word do you bring of the Bloodsail encampment to the south?'),
('605','0','0','Do you have those shards yet?  I\'ll give you a decent cut from the profits!'),
('606','25','25','Hey!  I don\'t like the look you\'re giving me, $gmister:lady;.'),
('607','0','0','Here here, $N.  Did you get Shaky\'s payment?'),
('608','1','0','What\'s the problem, $N? We need to attack before the Bloodsail Buccaneers do!'),
('609','0','0','$N, did you find those three dogs? Did you collect their valuables?'),
('610','1','0','I\'d never been beat before, you know, $N? Sure I\'d been cut, can\'t get in a knife fight without that, but he just smacked me on the side of the head, blacked me out. When I came to my blade was gone.$B$BAs much as my nickname might indicate, I still need a knife to fight, and for me, it has to be that one.'),
('611','1','0','Have you retrieved the Stone of the Tides for me, $N? I\'ve already cleared out a space and purchased a fine stand for it.'),
('613','6','6','Ahoy, $N! Have you yet found Maury\'s Key?'),
('614','3','3','Ahoy, $N! Did you find Gorlash? That chest was my favorite, and it has a hidden compartment that held my greatest treasures!'),
('615','1','0',NULL),
('616','1','0',NULL),
('617','0','0','If ya got no business with me, then move along, $N.'),
('618','1','0','Did you get my cutlass, $N?'),
('619','1','0','This is an abandoned lifeboat.  Printed along its side in scratched, faded paint are the words:$B$B\"Smotts\' Revenge\"'),
('620','1','0',NULL),
('621','0','0','Do you have the samples of Zanzil\'s Mixture??'),
('622','1','0','Hello, $N. Did you make it to Booty Bay? Did the goblin Krazek fix my pot??'),
('623','1','0','Yeah?'),
('624','1','0',''),
('625','1','0',''),
('626','1','0',''),
('627','1','0','Hello, $N. Did you have luck getting the bloodstone?'),
('628','1','0','I read somewhere that the saltwater crocilisks are slowly dying out... bad news for my business, isn\'t it?$b$bAnyways, I hope you have that elder saltwater crocolisk skin for me!'),
('629','0','0','I await the Tablet Shard, $N.'),
('630','0','0','I thank my ancestors someone has come to aid me. Do you have the key that will free me?'),
('631','1','0',NULL),
('632','6','0','Any sign of Ol\' Rustlocke, $N?'),
('633','1','5','The cache of explosives must be destroyed!'),
('634','1','0',NULL),
('635','1','0',NULL),
('636','1','0',NULL),
('637','1','0','You look as though you have traveled a great distance and seen much turmoil in your time, $C. These times we live in are trying on the soul. What news do you bring to me now?'),
('638','1','0',NULL),
('639','1','0','Have you located the first sigil yet? It is most likely carried on the person of one of the Syndicate agents in Stromgarde.'),
('640','0','0','Throm\'ka, $c. Zengu informed me that you required my assistance?'),
('641','1','0','$N! Do you have the second sigil?'),
('642','0','0','This cluster of shards looks much like the Shards of Myzrael.  But the same feeling of security does not pulse through them.'),
('643','1','0','Valorcall will not be easy to track down, $N. Mounted on horseback, he can cover ground quickly. Nonetheless, we must have his sigil.'),
('644','1','0','You\'ve returned, $N. Is the line of Ignaeus Trollbane broken?'),
('645','1','0','Etchings in the stone upon the face of the tomb of Trollbane match the glowing lines of the Sigil of Ignaeus...'),
('646','1','0','$N! Have you taken the sword?'),
('647','1','0','What\'s the good word, $R?'),
('648','1','0',NULL),
('649','1','0',NULL),
('650','1','0',NULL),
('651','1','0','This is the Stone of Inner Binding. It is the strongest of the binding stones and must be unlocked for the others to open.'),
('652','1','0','The Keystone is charged with tremendous geomantic energy.'),
('653','1','0',NULL),
('654','1','5','Well, did you get everything you needed? If you didn\'t and the power runs out, everything inside will be ruined and you\'ll have to start over.$B$BHey, don\'t look to me for sympathy; I\'m all about the Gadgetzan Water Company making a profit, and if that means selling you power sources until we can afford to import water in from the icy springs of Dun Morogh, so be it!'),
('655','1','0',NULL),
('656','1','0','The Shards of Myzrael are now strangely quiet.'),
('657','1','0',NULL),
('658','1','0','We appreciate your help in looking for that courier, $N.$B$BWhile you were gone, Kin saw an apothecary come out of that same house to the south of here. I\'m confident that they\'re up to no good--I just need proof of it before we go off and do something rash.$B$BHave you had any luck yet?'),
('659','1','0',NULL),
('660','1','0',NULL),
('661','1','0',NULL),
('662','0','0','How goes the search and recovery mission, $n?  We really need to get those Logs and Charts back from the Maiden\'s Folly and Spirit of Silverpine.$b$bIf the information from those sources were to fall into enemy hands, Fleet Master Seahorn would force us down the plank.$b$bThat is if we ever get out of this mess...'),
('663','1','0',NULL),
('664','1','0','Bah, maybe I should go kill those naga scum myself. It\'s obvious you\'re not goin\' to do it.$B$BMaybe I can find some knitting needles so you can keep yourself busy.'),
('665','1','0','This is no time to talk! The goggles need to be charged with the power of the stone!'),
('666','1','0','How did the goggles work? Did everything function properly? Adjustments can be made if necessary.$b$bOh, and I\'ll need those goggles back when you\'re done. I am sure Captain O\'Breen will have many uses for them later on.'),
('667','1','0',NULL),
('668','1','0','Ahoy, $C. What brings you to the bridge?'),
('669','1','0','What brings you to Booty Bay, $C?'),
('670','1','0','So was Seahorn impressed? I bet you his smile reached from Booty Bay to Ratchet.'),
('671','1','0','Once-cursed blood still runs through my veins, $N. If someone... something is summoning demons, it must be stopped.'),
('672','1','0','I will create an amulet that will give Gor\'mul some of the strength of the raptors. Perhaps that will awaken some flame within him...'),
('673','1','0','The burning in my blood... it grows by the day. The warlock must be stopped.'),
('674','1','0','What hope is there when the hand of a coward can slay the mightiest of the mightiest? What hope, I ask you!'),
('675','1','0',NULL),
('676','1','0','I have not the time to sharpen my axe, let alone leave the outpost to slay those beasts that would try and slay my kin.$B$BYou do not seem to have the experience of a grunt let alone a full-fledged warrior, what do you want, $N?'),
('677','1','0','If you have not yet completed my task, then perhaps you are a coward in heart as well as a tyro in war.'),
('678','1','0','You hesitate. Why? You have shown great strength thus far, $N. Do not fail me now.'),
('679','1','0','I see your courage finally wanes. It seems my instincts were correct about you: your strength is nothing compared to your bravado.$b$bReturn to me when the beast\'s head has been severed, or return never again.'),
('680','1','0','Near the Tower of Arathor--that is where you will find Or\'Kalar. His death will stop the attacks on Hammerfall and protect my husband\'s life.$B$BI see in your eyes that you think me weak--even dishonorable--for my silence. Some day you will learn what it is to love as I do. Perhaps then you will understand a different kind of strength and honor.$B$BIn the meantime, do as I ask, and slay Or\'Kalar.'),
('681','1','0','$N, with each passing hour our hold on Stromgarde grows more tenuous. You must make haste or our city will surely fall.'),
('682','1','0','Have you retrieved any Stromgarde Badges, $N? The Syndicate must learn they cannot profit from our dead.'),
('683','6','0','So you are $N the $C? News of your contributions to the Alliance has traveled quite far, you know?$B$BOn what business do you come before me today?'),
('684','1','0','Greetings, $C. You have a report to make?'),
('685','1','0','Hello. Do you have a report to submit?'),
('686','1','0',NULL),
('687','1','0',NULL),
('688','1','0',NULL),
('689','5','5','$N, $N, $N! Tell me you have enough Alterac Granite for me to begin my masterpiece in honor of Sully Balloo.'),
('690','5','5',NULL),
('691','1','0','Have you had any luck so far, $N?$B$B<Kryten makes some notes in his journal as he reads.>$B$BIf my research is correct, the tusks should come from any Witherbark troll. The medicine pouches come from the Witherbark witch doctors, and the strongest of the Witherbark shadow hunters should carry the special knife given to them after they\'ve completed their rites of passage. There\'s no way to tell which shadow hunters will have the knife until you do battle.'),
('692','1','0','Did you find those fragments?!?! You\'ll need the Scroll of Myzrael if you want to trap her again, before it\'s too late!'),
('693','1','0','Our goal is the wand, $N. Focus on that for now.'),
('694','1','0','$N, hello again. Have you found an azure agate yet?'),
('695','1','0',NULL),
('696','1','0','You do this, an\' I\'m sure Malin\'ll be more than pleased with you.'),
('697','1','0','Yes? You look vaguely familiar. I do apologize, but have we met? I get so busy I lose track.'),
('698','1','0','Lok\'tar, $C. Traveling through the swamps isn\'t a risk taken lightly. You\'re brave to test your mettle here.'),
('699','1','0','Good mead, a warm fire, an army of orcs and an arsenal of weapons... that\'s all we really need out here along the coast. I don\'t regret my position out here safeguarding Stonard, but it would be nice if we could one day get a burrow, or at least a tower.'),
('700','1','0',NULL),
('701','1','0','My preparations are made, all I require are the raptor hearts.'),
('702','1','0','Returned again have you? Indeed there is nothing more I could wish for now than more of Tor\'gan\'s pity.$B$BWhat have you for me this time? Perhaps a piece of brightly colored string? Or a length of rope to end this misery of mine...'),
('703','1','0','Hello, $N. Did you bring me my wings?'),
('704','6','6','Did you find those urns, $N? We must find the link between them and the troggs!'),
('705','1','0','Did you get my pearls?  I\'m almost out of flash bombs!'),
('706','1','0','How goes the hunt, $C?'),
('707','1','0',NULL),
('708','1','0',NULL),
('709','1','0','Did you find the tablet? It must hold secrets! Secrets to save us!'),
('710','6','0','This area\'s perfect for-- Could you hold these in place for a moment? Yes, just like that, along the vector normal. Now, what was I... Right. Perfect for testing my latest project. The raw materials, the open space... what more could an intelligent and enlightened practitioner of the arts ask for?'),
('711','0','0','I\'m most pleased, $N. My spells affected the smaller pieces just as I predicted. If this experiment is as successful as I foresee, then the elementals I\'ll be able to control will put anything summoned prior to this to shame.'),
('712','1','0','The stone slabs you found were ideal, $N. Lucien will be taking the extra ones back to Kharanos when we\'re done here. After all, they could prove useful again.$B$BFor instance, they\'d be a nice basis for a handy little shelter once I start looking into a multidisciplinary approach to high-yield explosives...'),
('713','6','0','Have you found the oil I need? It would be so helpful if you were able to find some.'),
('714','1','0','Yes, yes, yes. Just a moment.$b$b'),
('715','1','0','He\'s getting closer to finishing. How are things going on your end?'),
('716','1','0','I wouldn\'t wait too long to get that bracer, $N.$b$bWho knows what\'s going to happen next?'),
('717','1','0','Strong magics and powers held the drakes\' prison for so long, but we cannot allow any possibility that Blacklash and Hematus may be released.'),
('718','1','0','The desert\'s a bad place to be hungry, my friend, let me tell you that.$B$BHey... what\'s that over there...'),
('719','1','0','Not sure what the Shadowforge were lookin\' for, but they definitely had a purpose.'),
('720','1','0',NULL),
('721','1','0',NULL),
('722','1','0','The Shadowforge clan... is dangerous. Be careful. You must find the amulet.'),
('723','1','0','I\'d say it was a bad day, but this is the Badlands: every day\'s a bad day.'),
('724','1','0','Ah, yes. Another traveler seeking something from the dwarves.$B$BMa\'am, I\'m truly sorry, but I\'ve no time to answer meaningless questions right now.'),
('725','1','0','Hmm? Yes, $C.'),
('726','1','0',NULL),
('727','1','0','Hello. Welcome to my shop, but watch what you touch.$B$BKnowledge can be deadly.'),
('728','1','0','Ah, we have an eager $C, I see. Are you here to learn from my collection? Good!$B$BBut be warned: just as knowledge gives power to the strong...it will drive the weak mad.'),
('729','1','0',''),
('730','1','0',''),
('731','1','0','Is the prospector alive?'),
('732','1','0','The nomadic band of ogres travels between their camps across the Badlands; heat rising from the dry earth and the swirling winds will make it difficult to track their progress. I have heard that sometimes they travel through Camp Boff. If you are lost, you might try your search there.'),
('733','1','0','Well, I\'ve made do with what I could, but... it\'s not much. Have you found any more supplies?'),
('734','1','0',NULL),
('735','1','0','Do you have the relics for which I asked?'),
('736','0','0','How goes your mission, $c.'),
('737','1','0','Ho! You were gone a long time. Did you get the digest?'),
('738','1','0',NULL),
('739','1','0','Do you have news of Agmond\'s fate? Did you find him?'),
('741','1','0','What can I do for you, $R?'),
('742','1','0',NULL),
('743','1','0','The Windfuries are deadly foes. Their strength in battle is only rivaled by their desire for fresh meat.'),
('744','0','0','This headdress will certainly be a wonderful gift for my brother.'),
('745','1','0','If the Palemanes had respected the land and its inhabitants more, this conflict would have never occurred.'),
('746','0','0','Hello, $N.  Do you have the Broken Tools?  The dwarves\' digging will enrage the kodos of Mulgore.  This defilement must be stopped!'),
('747','1','0','Providing meat and feathers for the tribe is the first step in proving yourself as a $C before the Chief.'),
('748','1','0','Do you have the paws and talons, $N?'),
('749','1','0',NULL),
('750','1','0','If you can provide pelts for the tribe I will pass word along to my father, Chief Hawkwind, of your generous deeds.'),
('751','1','0','Hail, $N. Have you learned anything new about the Venture Co.\'s plans and operations in our homeland?$b$bIf they plan to exploit our lands as they have others, the Outrunners will be quick to put an end to it.'),
('752','1','0',NULL),
('753','1','0','You look as though you have returned from the plains. Do you have any word from Greatmother Hawkwind?'),
('754','1','0',NULL),
('755','1','0',NULL),
('756','1','0','$N, do you have the claws I sent you to gather? The Thunderhorn Water Well grows more tainted with each passing hour!'),
('757','21','0','Have you completed the Rite of Strength, $N? I require proof of your valor against the enemy of our tribe, the Bristlebacks.'),
('758','1','0',NULL),
('759','1','0','$N. Do you have the teeth I asked for?'),
('760','1','0',NULL),
('761','0','0','Have you found the swoops, $N.  Do you have their quills?'),
('762','1','0','Time is of the essence, $N. Ragnaros will not wait for us to prepare.'),
('763','1','0','What brings you to my village, $C?'),
('764','1','0','The Venture Co. was refused mining rights here in Mulgore, but it would seem that they do not take no for an answer. We tauren are not ones to mince words, however, and we have other ways of getting our message across.'),
('765','1','0','I seethe with anger at the thought of the atrocities the Venture Co. is willing to perpetrate against us in the name of profit.'),
('766','1','0','My fever grows worse and I find my mind drifting into delirious nightmares... I should have known that I wouldn\'t be able to handle a beast my grandfather was unable to defeat...$b$bDo you have the ingredients for the remedy? I fear if I do not clean the infection soon, it will be the death of me.'),
('767','1','0',NULL),
('768','1','0','Hello again. Have you been hunting? Do you have skins for me?'),
('769','1','0','Do you have my supplies, $N?'),
('770','1','0',NULL),
('771','1','0','Once you have gathered enough well stones from around the water wells and Ambercorn from beneath the trees, I will prepare the Water of the Seers for you.'),
('772','1','0',NULL),
('773','1','0',NULL),
('775','1','0',NULL),
('776','1','0','Have you tracked down Arra\'chea yet?'),
('777','1','0','<Without looking up from the shackles, Lotwil holds out a hand and waggles his fingers impatiently.>$B$BThe cog, $N, the cog!'),
('778','1','0','Not quite the outcome I was expecting. Could you get my shackles back?'),
('779','1','0','The Seal of the Earth lies here, with three recessed alcoves for the Amethyst Runestone, the Opal Runestone, and the Diamond Runestone.'),
('780','1','0','The aggression of the Battleboars is increasing. Have you sent them a clear message and brought back some snouts and flanks yet?'),
('781','1','0','You have a look of concern about you, $N. What news do you bring?'),
('782','1','0','Tho\'grun\'s betrayal... is there any wonder why the ogres are part of the Horde no longer? I will be glad to see him dead, and the Sign of the Earth returned.$B$BIf you\'ve not dispatched him yet, then waste no time going to Camp Boff.  It is to the southeast of Kargath.'),
('783','1','0',NULL),
('784','1','25','You have your orders, $N. The safety of Durotar is in question. Complete the task before you or hang your head in shame.$B$BShow your honor and defeat the humans of Tiragarde Keep.'),
('786','1','5','The centaurs have proven to be a consistent nuisance to the Horde. Their intentions to lay siege to our homeland cannot be tolerated.'),
('787','1','0',NULL),
('788','0','0','I hope you haven\'t returned to try and convince me that you have completed your task, $N? No, of course not. I would think better of you.'),
('789','1','0','The carapace of a scorpid isn\'t so thick that the strength of a determined $C will be deterred. Strike strongly and without doubt, and the scorpids should prove easy prey.'),
('790','16','0','Ahhh... my father always said I would never amount to much, and here, lying beneath a tree as life seeps away, I\'m afraid it looks like he was right.$b$bAt least I wish to die knowing that my last enemy in life lays dead.'),
('791','1','1','I fought proudly alongside the Warchief when these lands were pioneered. The scars of battle mark my skin.$b$bThe honor of the Horde has been upheld with the help of my axe and battlecry during the defeat of Archimonde, when the unholy alliance was made with the humans and elves, wrought from necessity.$b$bBut my position as watchman and provider has given me a new sense of worth.'),
('792','1','1','To prove yourself against the Burning Blade, you must first defeat its Vile Familiars. Return to me when you have done this.'),
('793','0','0','There are few enemies more deadly than dragonkind, and there were few dragons that fought as ferociously as Blacklash and Hematus.'),
('794','0','0','Is your task complete, $N? Do you have the Burning Blade Medallion?'),
('795','1','0','The Seal of the Earth lies here, with three recessed alcoves for the Amethyst Runestone, the Opal Runestone, and the Diamond Runestone.'),
('804','1','0',NULL),
('805','1','0',NULL),
('806','0','0','Did you find Fizzle, $N? He, and rest of the Burning Blade, must be scoured from our lands!'),
('808','0','0','Do you have my brother\'s skull, $N? Is he finally free?'),
('809','1','0',NULL),
('812','1','1','I\'m almost glad I can\'t return to Sen\'jin as I am now. My weakness and stupidity would surely be mocked.'),
('813','1','1','Remember, no matter what creature you hunt, you would do well to study it and understand its behavior. That knowledge could save your life.'),
('815','5','5','Breakfast, lunch, dinner! Who cares which meal it is? It still has to be cooked by someone--namely me!'),
('816','1','1','I pray that Kron will return to me, but I\'m almost certain I know his fate already.'),
('817','1','1','I remember my first tiger hunt, $N. I chose to hunt on the largest of the Echo Isles, and I sat perfectly still in the shadows of its foliage for almost a full day... watching... waiting.$b$bMy muscles were taut, and I was ready to strike. It was one of my greatest victories when that tiger finally took the bait.'),
('818','1','1','Time is the true test of your strength and will. Lose patience or give in to weakness, and your true self will be shown.'),
('819','0','0','Yes?'),
('821','0','0','How\'s the search going?'),
('822','6','6','You working hard at finding those ingredients, $N?'),
('823','1','0',NULL),
('824','1','0','Ah, hello there. I spend a great deal of time studying the water - all the elements really - so much so that sometimes I don\'t even notice people around me.$b$bIs there something I can help you with?'),
('825','1','1','Once we learn how the humans operate their strange machinery, we will stand a greater chance of defeating them in future battles.$b$bWith our new gained knowledge, the Horde only stands to grow in strength.'),
('826','0','0','Is Zalazane defeated, $N?'),
('827','1','0','Have you yet entered Skull Rock, $N? Do you have the Searing Collars?'),
('828','1','0',NULL),
('829','2','2','My most humble greetings, $C. How might I help my $R brother today?'),
('830','6','6','There is a look of concern on your face, $C. What have you there?'),
('831','1','0','Can you not see that I am busy? This had better be pressing....'),
('832','0','0','You have something vital to report. I can sense it behind your eyes.'),
('833','1','5','The Bristleback Interlopers must be driven away from our sacred burial ground, $n.'),
('834','0','0','I\'m great at what I do, don\'t get me wrong, but this is ridiculous! What am I supposed to do, build sand castles?'),
('835','1','0','You wouldn\'t think it from a guy like my boss Gazlowe, but he always seemed to know the score. \"Don\'t be afraid to take that big step,\" he said.$B$BHarpies won\'t stop bothering us and the caravans won\'t stop being attacked unless we do something about it, eh?'),
('836','1','0',NULL),
('837','1','0','Though they do possess some intelligence and some organization, I find it constantly amazing that the quilboars were able to capture and hold so much territory in Kalimdor. Perhaps they are more crafty an enemy than I give them credit for...'),
('838','1','0',NULL),
('840','15','0','What do you want, pup? If you\'re not here for recruitment, I don\'t have time for you.'),
('841','1','0','Well, have you got the ten water pouches?'),
('842','0','0','Well well well, what do we have here? Has Kargal deemed me worthy of another recruit?'),
('843','5','5','Many innocent tauren lost their lives or were forced off their ancestral birthplace when the dwarves of Bael Modan arrived. My land must be reclaimed!'),
('844','6','6','Have you collected the plainstrider beaks?'),
('845','0','0','How many zhevra have you slain?'),
('846','1','1','I see you are back, $N.$B$BWhile Khazgorm\'s death might delay the digging in my ancestral lands some, it will by no means bring a total end to the destruction.$B$BThe Keep at Bael Modan is an increasing military threat. Built to defend the dig site, it is now poised for offensive force as well.$B$BIf you have the ingredients I requested, I can fashion a charge that will make the hasty dwarves reconsider their actions here in the Barrens.'),
('847','1','0',NULL),
('848','0','0','Do you have the spores, $N? There is a concoction I must send to my associate in Thunder Bluff, which requires the spores...'),
('849','1','0','Once the dwarven flying machine has been destroyed I will feel the sweet satisfaction of revenge.'),
('850','0','0','Hello, $N. Do you have Barak\'s Head for me?'),
('851','0','0','Did you find Verog, $N?'),
('852','0','0','Is Hezrul defeated, $N?'),
('853','0','0','You have something from Apothecary Helbrim?'),
('854','1','0',NULL),
('855','0','0','How goes your hunting, $N?'),
('857','5','5','Where is the Tear of the Moons? I need it now! Need I say!'),
('858','1','0','Quick, we need to get out of here before someone gets suspicious!'),
('860','1','0',NULL),
('861','1','0','Greetings. There is an air about you that tells me much. Do we have business, you and I?'),
('862','6','0','Whack enough dig rats yet, $n?'),
('863','1','0','Can I help you?'),
('864','1','0','Welcome back. At least, welcome back if you have returned with a sealed testing kit. Otherwise, I will pretend not to notice your utter incompetence and spare my wrath from you until you do as you have been tasked and accomplish my task.'),
('865','0','0','Did you get the horns, $N? Those things are going to make me a fortune!'),
('866','1','0','Hello, $N. Did you get those root samples?'),
('867','0','0','Cut up enough of them yet? Keep slicing and taking trophies. I want 8 Witchwing talons.'),
('868','1','1','Be careful with the eggs you find, $N. If they break, they be no good to me.'),
('869','0','0','Do you have those heads, $N?'),
('870','1','0',NULL),
('871','1','0','The longer it takes to stop these attacks, the harder it will be to provide supplies for the people of the Crossroads.'),
('872','1','1','Cut off the head of their leader, and chaos ensues, $N. Learn this lesson well. It will aid you in the future.$B$BThe boars will flounder without direction, and we will be able to take back the Barrens.'),
('873','0','0','Fear not the waters, $R.'),
('874','1','0',NULL),
('875','0','0','Do you have 6 Harpy Lieutenant Rings yet? Justice must be dealt to them for their vicious attacks on the Horde.'),
('876','0','0','You\'re not getting anything until I see Serena\'s head.'),
('877','1','6','Have you been to the Stagnant Oasis? Was there a fissure beneath its waters?'),
('878','1','0','More information <snort> for the Horde when you\'ve killed the Bristleback\'s wise ones, $R. <snort> Not a moment earlier! Mangletooth is no fool.'),
('879','1','0','How goes your hunt, $R? <snort>$B$BThork thinks he knows the truth about who leads the raids against his people, <snort> but he shall learn how wrong he is if you are successful.$B$BMy death is inescapable, but you have caused great pain to my enemies, so Mangletooth regrets nothing. <snort>'),
('880','6','6','How goes your collection? Did you get the shells?'),
('881','0','0','The great cat calls to you, $N.'),
('882','0','0','$N, have you bested Ishamuhale?'),
('883','0','0','$N, when you approached I saw a new power in your stride. Tell me -- has your spirit met with the great Lakota\'mani?'),
('884','0','0','$N, there is a new power behind your eyes! You have met with the mighty Owatanka, have you not?'),
('885','0','0','There is new resolve within you, $N. A resolve born from pain...$B$BAre you burdened with the death of Washte Pawne?'),
('886','1','0',NULL),
('887','1','0','I don\'t even want to think about the profits I\'ve lost from pirate raiding, and now they set up camp on my doorstep? It\'s getting out of hand, Undermine\'s got to do something about it.'),
('888','1','1','Did you find my things, $N?'),
('889','1','0','Bring Mangletooth 10 blood shards and I will bless you with great speed. You will run with zhevra and the wind will be jealous of you.$B$BIt will not last long, but it should be enough to help you travel throughout the Barrens.'),
('890','0','0','Wares to send on the next ship, $N?'),
('891','5','5','My fleet is in peril with Captain Fairmount and her damned cannoneers blasting away from Northwatch Hold. I want her soldiers to pay as well. Fill my hand with medals from their dead and I will know that vengeance has been given to my fallen privateers.'),
('892','0','0','So, what did Dizzywig have to say?'),
('893','1','1','I, too, have doubts that the pathetic quilboars could attain any level of skill in the area of smithing, but I do as the Warchief commands, and I shall learn what I can about the Razormane tribe.$B$BI have had more menial tasks, and I do so willingly if it aids the orc people.'),
('894','1','0',NULL),
('895','0','0','What\'s happening? Something I can help you with? Goods to ship, perhaps an engineering job?'),
('896','0','0','If only we knew which one of the miners had found the emerald, it\'d be a walk in the park...'),
('897','6','6','You seemed troubled, $N. How go your lessons in the Barrens? Did you find something that disturbs you?'),
('898','1','0','Yes?'),
('899','1','1','The quilboar will pay for this, $N. I swear it.'),
('900','1','0','Blinking lights on the control console indicate that the main control valves have not been closed off.'),
('901','1','0','The console lights are dimmed and the gauges and dials all read at their zero positions, everything idling.'),
('902','1','0','Oh, you\'re back, $N! Do you have the samophlange?'),
('903','0','0','How goes your hunt, $N? Have you found the prowlers?'),
('905','1','0','Have you been to the nests, $N?'),
('906','6','0','Yes, what is it?'),
('907','0','0','Are the thunder lizards defeated, $N?'),
('908','1','0','Have you been successful in locating the fathom core? Without it we\'ll have no idea what the Twilight\'s Hammer is exactly up to down there.'),
('909','1','0','Ah, hello again $N. I was just reading the waves the sea, much like I always do. What brings you to the outpost?'),
('910','1','0','Are we there yet?'),
('911','1','0','Are we there yet?'),
('913','6','6','Is it done? Have you slain the thunderhawk?'),
('914','6','6','Memories of my nightmares haunt me, $N. Have you defeated the leaders of the fang and acquired their gems?'),
('915','1','0','I wish they\'d make more flavors of ice cream other than strawberry, but I guess I\'m lucky that strawberry is my favorite!'),
('916','6','6','Did you gather the venom sacs, $N?'),
('917','6','6','Have you been inside the Shadowthread Cave, $N? Did you find a spider egg?'),
('918','6','6','Do you have the seeds? I am eager to plant them.'),
('919','3','3','Hello, $N. Have you found any sprouts near the waters?'),
('920','0','1',NULL),
('921','1','1','The moonwells hold the waters of the Well of Eternity, the ancient source of magic that has wrought so many horrors upon our world.$B$BThe druids take advantage of its properties, and the Sentinels revere the wells as shrines to Elune, but sorcery is forbidden to all.'),
('922','2','0','Hello...$b$bAnd how may I help you?'),
('923','3','3','Have you been to Wellspring Lake, $N? Have you been hunting the timberlings there?'),
('924','1','0','The Demon Seed still exists. I can sense its power...'),
('925','1','0','When the orcs were alone and without friends, the tauren welcomed them to a strange land and shared with them without asking anything in return. That\'s honor, $N.'),
('926','1','0',''),
('927','1','0','$N! You have something for me?'),
('928','1','1','Greetings, $C. For what purpose do I owe the pleasure of our meeting?'),
('929','3','3','Hello again, $N. Have you completed your task?'),
('930','0','0','$N, you look like you have something to tell me. Do you have news concerning the timberlings?'),
('931','0','0','You have something for me?'),
('932','6','2','Did you kill Lord Melenas yet? It is vital that he be taken care of quickly and quietly, $N. His continued existence is an embarrassment to us all.'),
('933','1','0','At first the reports of crazed furbolg attacks were dismissed. Who could have thought that the peace-loving bear-men would turn to mindless rage? Yet another of the problems that plagues us here in our new home.'),
('934','1','0','Along with the druids, the Oracle Tree and the Arch $C have been carefully monitoring the growth of Teldrassil. But though we have a new home, our immortal lives have not been restored.'),
('935','0','0','I know that I did not summon you, so I cannot help but wonder why it is you have come to speak with me.$B$BWhatever it is, please make it quick.'),
('936','1','0',NULL),
('937','1','1','Their slashing talons and piercing beaks may prove a difficult match for your own abilities, $N, but I have faith that you will not fail in this task.'),
('938','1','0','Mist... It was my fault! The witches caught me off guard... I should not have let them take you...'),
('939','6','6','What is it, $C? You look concerned.'),
('940','1','0','Hmm... You come with the spirit of the forest strongly within you, $C. What business do you have with the Arch Druid of the Kaldorei?'),
('941','1','0','This planter is filled with soil, specially prepared by Denalan.'),
('942','1','0','What ya got there, friend?'),
('943','1','0','With the Stone of Relu I will be able to release the hidden secrets of my fossil as well as Remtravel\'s fossil from Darkshore, $N.'),
('944','1','0','The Master\'s Glaive, $N.$B$BGo there, then speak with me again.'),
('945','1','0',''),
('947','6','6','Do you have my mushrooms, $N? Have you been to the cave?'),
('948','1','0',NULL),
('949','1','0',NULL),
('950','1','0','$N. You return.'),
('951','1','0','$N. Has your rooting through the Ruins of Mathystra been fruitful?'),
('952','1','0','Ah. $C. How may Onu assist you?'),
('953','1','0','When you have studied the tablets and learned of Ameth\'Aran\'s fall, I will take the knowledge on to Auberdine, and inform the Circle of Ancients.'),
('954','1','0',NULL),
('955','1','0','Once I have the earrings, I will cast the spell to search for the whereabouts of the seal that binds me. For centuries I have thought on the freedom destroying the seal would bring to me... Perhaps those centuries have taken a toll upon my mind that I might never recover...'),
('956','0','0','The pillars of this shrine are as the bars of a prison to me, $N. No strength I still possess might break them, and no magic I wield might destroy them...$B$BFor a thousand years and more I have stared at them, wondering if at long last I outlived even the stone, would I be free? Or would it be invisible bars that held me then...'),
('957','1','0','In truth, $N, I am afraid... Afraid that your coming--all of this--is merely a figment of a deranged mind. Can you know the torture that this is? I... Please, you must go quickly.'),
('958','0','0','If only the tools of their undoing could have been destroyed in the cataclysm that destroyed our world... Nonetheless, we must do what we can to ensure that the horrors of our past are not repeated in the future.'),
('959','0','0','The dockmaster has been on my case ever since Mad Magglish made off with that 99-year-old port. I guess that bottle was intended as a gift for Gazlowe from none other than Baron Revilgaz himself.$B$BIf you\'re brave enough and patient enough to seek out Mad Magglish and get that port back, I\'ll see to it you get a nice reward.'),
('960','1','0',NULL),
('961','1','0',''),
('962','1','0','I am eager to see if you can gather enough Serpentbloom from the Wailing Caverns. I\'ve sent many to do my bidding but none have returned.'),
('963','1','1','With a great sorrow in my heart, I followed the Shan\'do Stormrage into hibernation, and took my sorrow to my dreams, sleeping for the passing of thousands of years.'),
('964','1','1','Kill many and kill often, $C - we\'ll need a decent supply of suitable skeletal fragments to make up the outer layer of the key. They don\'t call it a Skeleton Key for nothing, you know.'),
('965','1','0',NULL),
('966','6','6','Have you found any more of their scrolls? I should be able to piece together a larger picture of the cult if you can find them.'),
('967','6','0','You have some business with me, $C?'),
('968','3','0','Hello, $Gsir:madam;.$B$BMay I interest you in one of my tomes?'),
('969','11','11','Bring back da shards, and I be tellin\' you more!'),
('970','6','6','Have you acquired that soul gem?'),
('971','1','1','The journey to Ashenvale is long, and your task is not easy. But if you get me the manuscript, $N...then your reward will be great.'),
('973','6','6','You look a bit shaken up, $n. Are you well?'),
('974','1','1','I\'d go there myself, but... I\'m a little scared of the fire elementals there!'),
('975','1','0',''),
('976','1','0','The Sentinels have a great need for supplies to reinforce themselves in Darkshore.'),
('977','0','0','I\'ve just about finished attaching the fur, $N. Please, hurry back with those horns!'),
('978','6','6','Where could these powers have originated from? I think we are on the right track to find the answer, $N.'),
('979','1','0',NULL),
('980','1','0',NULL),
('981','1','0',NULL),
('982','1','1','The captains of those ships were good night elves, and they deserve a better fate than they were given. Perhaps tending to their personal effects will be the best way to put their spirits to rest.'),
('983','1','0','Buzzbox 827 sits with an eerie silence. A single flashing light indicates that it needs 6 Crawler Legs to be placed in its holding box.'),
('984','1','0','How goes your search, $N?'),
('985','1','1','Do not stay your hand from what must be done, child. I know how repulsive the idea of killing the creatures of the forest must be, but in this case it is necessary. No cure has been discovered for the corruption let loose upon the forest, and we must do what we can to halt its progress until one is found.'),
('986','1','0','I can\'t in good conscience permit you to seek Volcor until I\'ve crafted that cloak for you.'),
('990','1','0',NULL),
('991','1','0',NULL),
('992','6','0','Welcome back, Junior Surveyor $n!  Have you completed your assignment yet?'),
('993','0','0',''),
('994','1','0',''),
('995','1','0','Yes, $n?'),
('996','0','0','You have found a sickly, corrupted version of what appears to be a windblossom plant.  The berries that hang from the plant appear rotten and poisonous.  It desperately needs some sort of attention if it is to be turned back to normal.'),
('997','6','1','You have something for me?'),
('998','1','0','You have found a sickly, corrupted version of what appears to be a windblossom plant. The berries that hang from the plant appear rotten and poisonous. It desperately needs some sort of attention if it is to be turned back to normal.'),
('1000','1','0',NULL),
('1001','1','0','The machine\'s hatch is open and it seems to wait expectantly for 3 Thresher Eyes to be placed inside.'),
('1002','1','0','Though you have yet to place the 6 Moonstalker Fangs inside, you believe you hear the sounds of static and incoherent gnome ramblings coming from within. Could someone else have fixed the machine already?'),
('1003','1','0','You hear singing coming from Buzzbox 525.$b$b\"Though crawler wine\'s shweet, and thresher ale fine, and moonstalker moonshine ish grand. There\'s nothing sho dear, as a thistle bear beer, and shoon I shall have shome on hand!\"$b$bThe hatch is open and awaits the 4 grizzled scalps as you hear the song repeated over and over.'),
('1004','1','0',NULL),
('1007','0','0','Have you found the statuette, $N?'),
('1008','0','0','We cannot allow the naga to invade our coasts, $N.  It is vital that you go to the Zoram Strand and complete your mission.'),
('1009','0','0','It is said that the Ring of Zoram is the key to any lock within the city. Do you have it, $N?'),
('1010','6','6','Have you gathered the Bathran\'s Hair, $N?  The child\'s health grows weaker by the hour...'),
('1011','6','6','Did you find the camp, $N? Do you have a bottle of disease?'),
('1012','1','0','The anguish of the Dor\'danil druids still haunt my dreams, $N. You must destroy their leaders!'),
('1013','1','0','Did you find the book, $N?'),
('1014','1','1','With Arugal\'s death we stand to increase the Dark Lady\'s stronghold on Lordaeron.'),
('1015','1','0',NULL),
('1016','1','1','Since you must destroy the bracers to kill the elementals, it will probably be difficult to find the specific ones that contain the information the divining scroll needs. You can trade bracers with others in order to obtain the ones you need, or perhaps you have the divined paper already?'),
('1017','6','6','Is it done? Is Sarilus Foulborne dead?'),
('1018','1','0',NULL),
('1019','1','0',NULL),
('1020','1','0','I must apologize, for I have no time to speak.  My child, Relara, is deathly ill!'),
('1021','1','0',NULL),
('1022','1','0','The tome of the shrine is a mysterious object. It is not a book in the traditional sense. The leaves of the tome were blessed by Mel\'Thandris herself, and records events of import in its pages.$B$BIt is hard for me to explain. If you go to the shrine, you will understand.'),
('1023','2','2','Ah, welcome back, $N.'),
('1024','1','0','Hello. How are you?'),
('1025','1','0','The furbolg were not always our enemy, $N. But times change, and it is no longer a time of peace here in these dark woods.'),
('1026','1','0','It upsets me so that the treants have become corrupt. I wish I could do more to help them.'),
('1027','1','0','Did you find the final piece of the rod, $N?'),
('1028','1','0','You can sense a subtle yet powerful force within the shrine and surrounding trees.$B$BYou begin placing the rod within the shrine and a soft thrumming noise emits from around you as the shrine begins to glow...'),
('1029','1','0',NULL),
('1030','1','0',NULL),
('1031','1','0','Have you found them? What did Anilia say? Where is she?'),
('1032','1','0','Please, help me avenge Anilia\'s death.'),
('1033','6','6','$N, did you find Iris Lake? Do you have the Tear?'),
('1034','6','6','Do you yet have the Stardust, $N?'),
('1035','6','6','Did you face the Shadethicket Oracle, $N? If so, then please hand me the fallen moonstone. Relara has strength left for only a few more breaths!'),
('1036','1','0',NULL),
('1037','1','0',NULL),
('1038','0','0','What\'d you find out?'),
('1039','1','0',NULL),
('1040','1','0',NULL),
('1041','1','0',NULL),
('1042','1','0',NULL),
('1043','1','1','The woods are perilous for the unprepared. Keep your weapons close at hand and your wits even closer, or your next journey into the haunted forest may be your last.'),
('1044','1','0',NULL),
('1045','0','0','Have you slain Ran yet, my friend?$B$BEven the Night elves do not truly deserve his wrath. His hatred burns even brighter than my own, but his mind is no longer his own. He is a threat to all the natural creatures of this forest.'),
('1046','6','0','The Sentinels do what they can here in Ashenvale, but it\'s thanks to $rs like you that we have gained the ground we have.'),
('1047','1','0',NULL),
('1048','1','0','Perhaps I was not explicit in my orders, $c. I want High Inquisitor Whitemane killed once and for all. And while you\'re at it, take out her top brass as well.$B$BKill that zealot, Scarlet Commander Mograine. Lay waste to Herod, the Scarlet Champion. And slaughter Houndmaster Loksey and his filthy mutts too.$B$BNow begone!'),
('1049','1','0','Cairne is a brave and noble leader and I would trust him with my own life. But it is others that I do not trust in this political climate.$b$bOnce I have a chance to gather all the knowledge available I can provide sound council to the Chieftain.$b$bHave you had a chance to travel to Tirisfal Glades? To the Scarlet Monastery? The Compendium of the Fallen is just one piece in this complicated puzzle...'),
('1050','1','1','The Monastery was a seminary for Paladins-in-training. Once a stronghold of the Light, it fell into the hands of the crazed zealots of the Scarlet Crusade.$b$bThe Crusade believed their goal a noble one: to purify the land of the undead plague. But insanity tainted their plight and now they stand enemies to all.$b$bBring Mythology of the Titans to me so I can study it and house it here in Ironforge.$b$bThe corrupt halls of the Monastery are no place for such a historical treasure.'),
('1051','1','0','What do you want, stranger?'),
('1052','6','0','Who goes there? What do you want from me?'),
('1053','1','5','The corruption in the Monastery will not end until the highest ranking officials have been removed.$b$bIn the name of the Light, slay High Inquisitor Whitemane, Scarlet Commander Mograine,  Herod, the Scarlet Champion and Houndmaster Loksey. Once they have fallen, perhaps the true cause can be rekindled. Until then, anyone who crosses the path of the Crusade lies in peril.$b$bVenture forth from Southshore and make it so!'),
('1054','1','1','The furbolgs\' corruption has caused Ashenvale to become a fraction of its former glory.'),
('1055','1','0',NULL),
('1056','1','0',NULL),
('1057','1','0','There is much work to be done before the Charred Vale can be restored to the lush forest it once was.$B$BClear the area of those foul menaces, $N! Only then can we begin to reclaim what belongs to nature.'),
('1058','11','11','Look at our poor little elf friends. All caged up with no forest to frolic in!$b$bNow were you able to find me some sap? How about the whiskers from the twilight runners? Don\'t suppose you have that fey dragon scale on you?$b$bAnd eyes! I\'ll need so many eyes! You just can\'t mix up a fierce forest magic brew without a good helping of eyes!'),
('1059','1','0',NULL),
('1060','0','0','You seem a shady character. You have something for me to see?'),
('1061','1','0',NULL),
('1062','1','1','The Greatwood Vale lies to the northwest, $N. Go. Strike fear into those who would pillage this land!'),
('1063','1','0',NULL),
('1064','1','0',NULL),
('1065','1','0','Ah, are you here with my new test subjects?'),
('1066','6','6','Did you find the Syndicate Shadow Mages, and collect from them the blood?'),
('1067','6','0','You have returned, $N. Do you bring aid from Apothecary Lydon?'),
('1068','1','1','The tree spirits wail at the loss of their brethren, $N. You must destroy the shredders XT:4 and XT:9, or I fear Stonetalon will never be healed.'),
('1069','1','1','Did you get the eggs, $N? I already made a shipping deal with Wharfmaster Dizzywig!'),
('1070','1','0',NULL),
('1071','1','6','How goes the battle on your end, $N?'),
('1072','1','0',NULL),
('1073','6','6','I can\'t make any Nitromirglyceronium if I don\'t have the potions... they\'re vital to its creation.'),
('1074','0','0','Ah, goodie goodie, you\'re back.'),
('1075','1','0',NULL),
('1076','6','6','Hello, $N. Have you found the component I need?'),
('1077','5','0','Haha! you\'re back! Do you have it? Do you have the spell?'),
('1078','2','2','Hello again, $N.$B$BHave you already returned from the Vale in Stonetalon with those scales?'),
('1079','6','6','Did you get the plans, $N?'),
('1080','6','6','How\'d it go, $N?'),
('1081','1','0',NULL),
('1082','1','0',NULL),
('1083','0','0','The first time I saw the Charred Vale I almost wept, $N.'),
('1084','1','1','I have a feeling Gaxim will find a use for the shrapnel regardless of how the Venture Co. has used it in the past.'),
('1085','1','0',NULL),
('1086','1','0','You must find the Venture Company airport if it exists, $N.'),
('1087','0','0','Here, channeling magic is like drawing water from a well with a bucket full of holes.'),
('1088','0','0','When my master bade me to the peak of Stonetalon, I expected that all I would need was to lay waste to the night elves that crawled the sacred ruins of our ancient temple of Azshara, their touch despoiling its sanctity... but Ordanus had slipped my grasp.'),
('1089','1','0','Three keyholes are carved into the stone.'),
('1090','1','0',NULL),
('1091','6','0','Yes, $N? What can I do for you?'),
('1092','0','0','Something I can help you with?'),
('1093','0','0','Did you find those plans? I\'m eager to impress the new boss. Hopefully, once he\'s convinced of my loyalty--well, as much as he can be convinced... goblin\'s honor, you know?--he\'ll feel comfortable making use of my rather impressive genius.'),
('1094','3','0','Hello there! How can I help you?'),
('1095','1','0',NULL),
('1096','0','0','Sputtervalve will want some sort of proof that Gerenzo\'s dead. I think his mechanical arm will probably do.'),
('1097','1','0',NULL),
('1098','1','0',NULL),
('1100','6','0','From your look of concern, I can tell that something is amiss....'),
('1101','1','1','So long as Charlga Razorflank is mustering a force in Razorfen Kraul, these lands are in great danger.'),
('1102','1','0','Once I know the foul beasts of Razorfen Kraul have been driven from their foul lair, I will be able to rest in peace, knowing that revenge has been served.$b$bHave you the driven the quilboar from the Kraul? Do you bring to me good news in the form of Razorflank\'s heart?'),
('1103','1','0','Ya have the sapta, $G brotha:sista;?$B$BI know another that had trouble after defeating da corrupt water spirit--seems he waited too long and he came out of the spirit world too quick fer his taste. Hate to see dat happen to another, so I\'ll just wait here fer a bit to make sure no one else be needin\' me help.'),
('1104','6','6','Hi hi hi! Did you get that venom??'),
('1105','1','1','My brother is making progress with his new fuel design, and that has me worried. I need to start work on a tortoise shell fuel tank as soon as possible!'),
('1106','35','0','Well, you found me. Good for you.$b$bAre you here about that axe I made for Gath\'Ilzogg? Or are you here to reclaim Duchess Pamay\'s honor?$b$bActually, I don\'t care which it is. If you\'re here to fight, then let\'s get it over with...'),
('1107','6','6','Do you have the tail fins?  If I can\'t protect our car from its own speed, then it won\'t last long in these races.'),
('1108','6','6','Did you find any indurium flakes, $N. I have my forge heated up and ready to test them.'),
('1109','1','0','Ah, I see you have returned. Were you able to procure any Kraul Guano?'),
('1110','6','6','$N, have you been out into the Flats? Did you bring back that load of parts I wanted?'),
('1111','0','0','Speak up! Tell me, are you dropping off or picking up?'),
('1112','0','0','Did you make it to Ratchet and get those parts?'),
('1113','1','0','Have you returned from the Scarlet Monastery? I\'ll need many hearts for this delightful experiment!$b$bNo doubt, Varimathras and the Dark Lady will be pleased to be rid of the Scarlet Scum as well...'),
('1114','0','0','You have something for me? That\'s great! let\'s see it!'),
('1115','1','0',NULL),
('1116','6','6','Back so soon? Do you have my dream dust?'),
('1117','6','0','Did you get anything on Nazz Steamboil? Anything he might want to keep a secret??'),
('1118','3','0','Hello hello. And what brings a noble $R such as you down to Booty Bay?'),
('1119','3','0','Hello, $N. Was Fizzlebub able to help us?'),
('1120','6','0','Hi! You have something for me?'),
('1121','6','0','What are you looking at?'),
('1122','1','0','Hello $N. How\'d that stout work out? It\'s strong stuff, isn\'t it?'),
('1123','1','0',NULL),
('1124','1','0','This is a dangerous land to be so casual, $C. What brings you to the wastes of Silithus?'),
('1125','1','1','Alliance or Horde, it doesn\'t matter - no being deserves to be trapped on this world as a tortured spirit.  The freeing of these souls will make things right, $N.'),
('1126','6','6','Well, did it work? You\'re still in one piece, which is good news. Did you find anything?'),
('1127','1','0','Do you have those Zanzil mixtures yet, $N?'),
('1130','1','0',NULL),
('1131','0','0','Have you defeated the foul Steelsnap, $N?'),
('1132','1','0',NULL),
('1133','1','2',NULL),
('1134','0','0','Do you have the pridewing venom sacs, $N? We cannot allow the orcs to use the beasts\' poisons against us!'),
('1135','1','0','Did you find Highperch, $N? Any luck with the wyverns there?'),
('1136','0','0','Have you been to the Alterac Mountains, $N? Did you face the elusive Frostmaw?'),
('1137','1','0',NULL),
('1138','0','0','...lemon crab, whipper root crab, and Ironforge surprise crab.  That\'s about it.$B$BOh, hello there $N.  Do you have them fine crab chunks I was telling you about?'),
('1139','1','0','Hammertoe\'s quest must be actualized, $N. I owe him that much.$B$BYour return to Uldaman is imperative not only to that goal, but also to the safety of all dwarven kind. With the tablet in the hands of the Dark Irons who knows how powerful their army of golems would become.'),
('1140','1','1','I heard whisper once that the satyrs\' history is somehow related to that of the night elves, but I have found my esteemed hosts reticent to speak of the matter.'),
('1141','1','1','There\'s plenty of good dishes you use Darkshore groupers for.  They\'re good to eat, but I think it\'s more fun catching them.$B$BYou caught any Darkshore groupers yet?'),
('1142','1','0','What brings you to my home, $R?'),
('1143','1','1','Athrikus Narassin is an ancient and powerful warlock. Perhaps we should wait for Delgren\'s assistance, but he obviously had much faith in you to send you alone.'),
('1144','1','0',NULL),
('1145','25','0','I envy you, $C. You have the look of someone who\'s been outside the walls of Orgrimmar for a while.$B$BI myself would travel in the name of the Warchief if Thrall didn\'t have need of my skills here in the city. But he leads us well, and I trust his judgement - I remain here for as long as he needs me.'),
('1146','1','0','War brings my group and I to the Shimmering Flats, $C. What brings you here?'),
('1147','1','0','With the amount of travelers heading out to the Flats for those races, I\'m sure we can convince enough adventure seekers to help push back those insects. My party and I won\'t be able to leave until we do.'),
('1148','1','1','Ah, it been a long time since you\'ve come to see me, $N. What can I do for you today? You be looking like you\'ve seen the face of battle recently. Good... good for the Horde and good for you. The more battle you\'ve seen, the more helpful you\'ll be; stronger, too.'),
('1149','1','0','Faith. It is far more important than some realize.$B$BIt does not matter what you believe sometimes. It is just important that you believe in something.'),
('1150','1','1','You must be prepared spiritually, physically and mentally for the challenges that lie ahead of you.$b$bToo often do we rush forward before we are ready. I consider it my duty to the youth, no matter which tribe they belong to, to prepare them for the dangers they may face after they leave the sanctity of their home.'),
('1151','1','1','Rok\'Alim is also called the Pounder by the centaur tribes in Thousand Needles because of the thundering his fists make as he pummels the creatures brave, or stupid, enough to stand in his path.'),
('1152','1','0',NULL),
('1153','1','1','I saw the travelers again - the ones that would not sell me a sample of the ore. I spit at them for not helping the warchief.$B$BMay they die in battle like cowards and not like warriors as should be the right of all people who ally themselves with the Horde.'),
('1154','1','1','Bring me the book after you\'ve studied it. I will not ask you your question until after you have given me the book.'),
('1159','1','0',NULL),
('1160','1','1','I hope you made the Scarlet Crusade suffer some before stealing the book from them.$b$bMy views of their kind are not unwarranted. The Crusade may have been followers of the Light at one time, but now, they seek to destroy any creatures that have not sided with their religion. They believe all undead, Forsaken or otherwise, must be cleansed, and those traveling in their lands must either be insane, or subject to the undead\'s powerful magics. Idiots. Idiots and fools; all of them.'),
('1164','5','0','Kill them all and bring me their heads!'),
('1166','0','0','Me thirsty for grog. Me miss snuff too. Where is strongbox? You go get for Overlord Mok\'Morokk.$b$bGo find south in old home. Me too busy leading ogres to get.'),
('1167','1','0',NULL),
('1168','1','0','Mok\'Morokk tell all ogres to stay and keep this place safe. Me think ogres need to kill black dragon army and get old home back.$b$bYou help ogres get home back. Help ogres get revenge.'),
('1169','0','0','With the hearts and tongues of scorched offspring of the black dragon army, I can decipher what wretched beast introduced her spawn into our home. Perhaps with a greater knowledge of our aggressors, we can seek to destroy them once and for all and reclaim Stonemaul Village from ruin.$b$bOf course, convincing Mok\'Morokk to move his lethargic, fat mass out of this muck hole is going to be an epic quest in and of itself...'),
('1170','1','0',NULL),
('1171','1','0',NULL),
('1172','1','0','You must hurry to the Dragonmurk, $n. With Onyxia\'s eggs riddled around the Wyrmbog, we face overwhelming numbers unless something is done quickly.$b$bDestroy her eggs! Don\'t let the black dragon plague spread across our homeland!'),
('1173','1','0','I thought you were going to attempt to drive Mok\'Morokk out of the village. Instead you have come to me to chat?'),
('1175','1','0','It\'s bad enough having to clear out the wreckage of the racers without having to pick them out of burnt animal parts.'),
('1176','6','6','Do you have those bones for me? I was just about to start working on lightening the steering rig, but I don\'t want to open her up without all the parts I need.'),
('1177','0','0','Gimme food or me eat you.'),
('1178','1','0',NULL),
('1179','5','0','Watch where you\'re stepping!  Watch watch watch!!  This is delicate stuff you see here, and if we\'re to win then it must all work perfectly!'),
('1180','1','0',''),
('1181','1','0',NULL),
('1182','0','0','Much as I hate to admit it, that gnome team they have out there is pretty good. Our boys need every edge they can get.'),
('1183','1','0','$N! Did you manage to track down the fuel regulator?'),
('1184','1','0',NULL),
('1185','1','0',NULL),
('1186','1','0',NULL),
('1187','0','0','How\'m I supposed to show my face around the track without a little extra kick to get me going? It\'s a travesty, I tell you.'),
('1188','0','0','As I\'m sure you know, the Gizmorium can service all of your tinkering needs! How can I help you?'),
('1189','1','0','Can you believe Pozzik put a bucket of sand on the racer? How am I supposed to hit my maximum speed with a bucket of sand under the seat?'),
('1190','1','0',NULL),
('1191','1','0',NULL),
('1192','1','1','I\'d like to integrate indurium into different parts of our racers, but I need large amounts of raw indurium to create these parts.$B$BYou can find indurium ore in the Uldaman excavation in the Badlands, across the sea in Khaz Modan.$B$BThe gnomes are getting their own supply of it, so it\'s important we get our own to keep pace with them.'),
('1193','1','0','A large, broken trap lies before you. From the looks of it, the ogres have tried to repair the trap but to no avail. A hastily written note lies next to the trap, and strangely enough it details exactly what is needed to repair it: a thorium widget and some frost oil. Were the trap repaired, an ogre passing near it might get trapped, and could be avoided.$b$bClearly, it would seem fortuitous that very few ogres know how to read.$b$bClearly.'),
('1194','1','0',NULL),
('1195','1','1','Once we have the filled phial, we can send it along to my associate, Rau, in the Thousand Needles. He was the one who requested the phial of water, so he\'ll better know how we can make use of it.'),
('1196','6','0','I don\'t suppose you\'ve been sent by Zangen, hm?'),
('1197','6','6','I am eager to put my hands upon the Cloven Hoof. Have you taken it yet?'),
('1198','1','0',NULL),
('1199','1','1','Blackfathom Deeps was once an ancient night elf temple. It once housed a most powerful moonwell. Who knows what evil brews there now at the hands of the Twilight\'s Hammer.$B$BHave you made any progress in ridding their presence?'),
('1200','1','1','Time is a precious commodity, $C.$B$BMy role here in Darnassus is to ensure that the Argent Dawn thrives and that the evil forces encroaching upon Kalimdor are thwarted.$B$BState your business quickly or be on your way.'),
('1201','1','0','Did you find the infiltrators, $N?'),
('1202','0','0','Did you find the documents, $N?  They hold information vital to the stability of the Alliance and, hence, vital to the security of the Horde.'),
('1203','1','0','You have my blade??'),
('1204','1','0','Did you get the forked tongues?'),
('1205','0','0','Do you have the tooth of Deadmire, $N?  Have you ended the creature\'s suffering?'),
('1206','1','0','Where are those eyes?'),
('1218','6','0','Spice.  We could all use some spice in our life.  You agree?'),
('1219','1','0','Do you have a report to make?'),
('1220','1','0','You have something for me?'),
('1221','0','0','Do you have the tubers, $N?'),
('1222','1','0','Have you seen Mr. Ignatz? I sent him into the swamp some time ago and he hasn\'t returned!'),
('1238','1','0','You have something for me?'),
('1239','1','0','You have another matter to report, $N?'),
('1240','1','0','There is an angry spirit about you, $gbrother:sister;. What brings you to Kin\'weelay?'),
('1241','1','0','Hmph, you better have good reason to interrupt a man and his fishin\'. I don\'t take kindly to peddlers, let alone beggars.'),
('1242','6','0','Hello, $N. Is there something I can do for you? Perhaps you\'d like to try some of our special Trias cheddar? Or a block of Darnassian bleu?'),
('1243','6','0','Not too safe to be traveling about in the woods, $N. Be careful, and if you see anything suspicious or dangerous, contact the Watchers immediately. Don\'t try and take anything on yourself. We\'re not responsible for anything terrible that might happen to you.$B$BBut we both know you\'re gonna ignore me and fight whatever comes out of the darkness anyway, don\'t we? Haha, yeah, you adventurer types... all the same.'),
('1244','1','1','Be careful out there, $N. I know Trias was the one to send you here, but that doesn\'t mean there isn\'t anything lurking out in the woods that couldn\'t cause you some trouble... especially with you investigating the Defias.'),
('1245','6','6','I see you\'re back, and in one piece. We both know you\'re not here for cheese, so let\'s cut out the pleasantries. Was Backus any help, or have you even left for Duskwood yet?'),
('1246','14','0',NULL),
('1247','1','0',NULL),
